[As mentioned in the articles above, one of the companies involved in the
current recall (Baxter) was associated with an earlier recall of dialyzers
in late 2001, which was covered by ProMED-mail (see references below). The
9 Nov 2002 ProMED-mail posting (see: Unexplained dialysis deaths -
multicountry (03) 20011109.2777) there was the FDA recall notice for
specific dialyzers produced by Baxter that were implicated in 50 deaths
occurring in Spain, Croatia, Italy, Germany, Taiwan, Colombia, and the USA
(Texas and Nebraska). <http://www.fda.gov/cdrh/recalls/dialyzers110701.html>
At that time, the clinical syndrome associated with these deaths was
described as: "Most of the dialysis patients who died experienced shortness
of breath, chest tightness, cardiac arrest or stroke symptoms within hours
of being dialyzed." At that time, results of preliminary tests suggested
that a perfluorohydrocarbon-based performance fluid used in a manufacturing
step may have played a role in the deaths of these patients.
A follow-up discussion on the etiology of this episode can be found on
renal web, with references to published articles on the episode. The
perfluorohydrocarbon use was concluded to be the etiology of this incident.
<http://www.renalweb.com/letters/shaldon.htm>
In this current alert, there is no information on the clinical illnesses of
the dialysis patients leading to this alert. There is a suggestion in the
second article (from Reuters Health) that the combination of the specific
tubing (from another manufacturer) if used with the specific dialysis
machine could lead to kinking of the tubing. In the absence of information
on the clinical illnesses related to the presumed dialysis session, it is
very difficult to speculate on the possible causative etiology. Clearly a
cluster of deaths in a short period of time (2 weeks) associated with a
specific manufacturer(s) equipment/combination warrants an immediate
investigation. Given the prior history of a multinational distribution of
dialysis equipment, one can't help but wonder if this event is a
tip-of-the-iceberg phenomenon that has been occurring internationally.
More information on this current alert as well as information from other
countries (perhaps as a result of active surveillance following the issue
of this alert) would be very much appreciated. - Mod.MPP]
